Course.Title: LIFE-SPAN DEVELOPMENTAL PSY
Course.Description: This course examines the psychological development of the individual across the lifespan. The influence of biological, sociological, and historical changes on psychological developments are discussed. Developmental concepts and theories are reviewed and applied in the study of the different stages of life.
